Package: QAIDR
Title: Quality Assessment for Interval-Based Dimensionality Reduction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Han-Ming", "Wu", , "hmwu@stat.ntpu.edu.tw", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0656-374X"))
Description: Provides quality and behavior indices for evaluating
    interval-based dimensionality reduction (DR) methods using co-ranking
    matrices. Supports multiple interval distance metrics (Euclidean,
    Hausdorff, Ichino-Yaguchi, L2-Wasserstein) and assessment criteria
    (Trustworthiness & Continuity, MRRE, LCMC). Includes wrappers for
    symbolic PCA methods, interval MDS, and interval UMAP, as well as
    permutation tests for statistical significance.
